    bibo:volume "1034" ;
    dc:creator "Lopes-Andrade, Cristiano; Lawrence, John F." ;
    dc:date "2005" ;
    dc:title "Phellinocis, a new genus of Neotropical Ciidae (Coleoptera: Tenebrionoidea)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273237>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273239>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273242>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273240>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273241> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273237>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 4. Phellinocis erwini sp. nov., male. 1. Body, dorsal view. 2. Anterior part of pronotum and head, dorsal view. 3. Part of elytra (arrow), pterothorax and abdomen, ventral view. 4. Base of abdomen, ventral view, showing setal patch (arrow). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Fig. 1); 0.1 mm (Figs. 2, 4); 0.3 mm (Fig. 3)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273237/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273239>
    dc:description "FIGURES 6 – 11. Phellinocis romualdoi sp. nov., male (if not specified). 6. Body, dorsal view. 7. Anterior part of pronotum and head, dorsal view. 8. Female antenna (arrow pointing to sensillifer on apical antennomere). 9. Antennae of male (A) and female (antennomeres 7 and 8 missing) (B). 10. Prosternum, showing the laminate prosternal process (arrow). 11. Protibia, showing two teeth at outer apex (arrow). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Fig. 6); 0.1 mm (Fig. 7 – 11)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273239/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273242>
    dc:description "FIGURES 17 – 20. Phellinocis thayerae sp. nov., male. 17. Body, dorsal view. 18. Anterior part of pronotum and head, dorsal view. 19. Part of elytra (arrow) and abdomen, ventral view. 20. Base of abdomen, ventral view, showing setal patch (arrow). Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Fig. 17); 0.1 mm (Figs. 18, 20); 0.3 mm (Fig. 19)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273242/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273240>
    dc:description "FIGURES 12 – 15. Phellinocis romualdoi sp. nov., male (if not specified). 12. Part of elytra (arrow) and abdomen, ventral view. 13. Base of abdomen, ventral view, showing setal patch (arrow). 14. Male setal patch (arrow). 15. Female setal patch (arrow). Scale bars: 0.3 mm (Fig. 12); 0.1 mm (Fig. 13); 0.5 mm (Figs. 14 – 15)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273240/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.273241>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Phellinocis romualdoi sp. nov., male genitalia showing eighth sternite (viii­S), ninth segment (ix), basal piece (bp), tegmen (teg) and median lobe (ml). Note enlarged, hooked apices of" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/273241/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

